12 SUMMARY
1133 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, reduces one-time
1144 funding by $200,000, instead of $800,000 as in the bill, to the 7 community colleges to
1155 continue offering student scholarships through the State's free community college tuition
1166 program for eligible persons who graduate high school or obtain the equivalent of a high
1177 school diploma in 2024 or 2025 in fiscal year 2025-26. The amendment appropriates
1188 $200,000 on a one-time basis to the Maine Fire Service Institute.
